{"word":"H281 - אֲחִיָּה - ʼĂchîyâh - akh-ee-yaw - Ahiah","slug":"H281","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֲחִיָּה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼĂchîyâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>akh-ee-yaw"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Ahiah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>אחיּהוּ אחיּה</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>'ăchı̂yâh 'ăchı̂yâhû</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>akh-ee-yaw</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Ahiah or Ahijah = \"brother of Jehovah (Yahu)\" <ol><li>grandson of Phinehas</li><li>scribe of Solomon</li><li>a prophet who predicted the revolt of the Northern tribes</li><li>father of Baasha, who usurped the Northern throne</li><li>grandson of Hezron (or mother of 1-4 above)</li><li>a Benjamite, son of Ehud</li><li>one of David's heroes</li><li>a Levite during David's time</li><li>a chief man under Nehemiah</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H251\">H251</a> and <a href=\"#/H3050\">H3050</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2361\">H2361</a>, <a href=\"#/H2438\">H2438</a>, <a href=\"#/H251\">H251</a>, <a href=\"#/H256\">H256</a>, <a href=\"#/H257\">H257</a>, <a href=\"#/H260\">H260</a>, <a href=\"#/H264\">H264</a>, <a href=\"#/H267\">H267</a>, <a href=\"#/H269\">H269</a>, <a href=\"#/H277\">H277</a>, <a href=\"#/H279\">H279</a>, <a href=\"#/H282\">H282</a>, <a href=\"#/H283\">H283</a>, <a href=\"#/H284\">H284</a>, <a href=\"#/H285\">H285</a>, <a href=\"#/H286\">H286</a>, <a href=\"#/H287\">H287</a>, <a href=\"#/H288\">H288</a>, <a href=\"#/H289\">H289</a>, <a href=\"#/H290\">H290</a>, <a href=\"#/H291\">H291</a>, <a href=\"#/H292\">H292</a>, <a href=\"#/H293\">H293</a>, <a href=\"#/H294\">H294</a>, <a href=\"#/H295\">H295</a>, <a href=\"#/H296\">H296</a>, <a href=\"#/H297\">H297</a>, <a href=\"#/H2